/*
 * Rage Forest 2026
 * Edited by T-West, June 2026.
 * Based upon the map Black Forest by Ensemble Studios.
 * Various previous versions of Rage Forest were edited by Gentle.
 * Furthermore, the 1v1 version of the map is based on T-West's map
 * from MembTV Warlords V, and the 2v2 version is based on T-West's map
 * from The Cartographers II.
 *
 * This map script supports all standard game modes:
 *
 * - 1v1 on a Tiny Map
 * - 2v2 on a Medium Map
 * - 3v3 on a Normal Map
 * - 4v4 on a Large Map
 *
 * Additionally, settings for all combinations of players, teams, map sizes,
 * victory conditions, and other settings are supported. But they do not
 * receive the same attention to detail that the standard settings do.
 *
 * On all of these game modes, attempts are made to ensure that teams receive
 * the same number of ponds. Pond positioning may still visually produce uneven
 * pond numbers, particularly when a pond for one team spawns towards the front
 * of a flank player's base. Ponds may also spawn trapped within forests. Both
 * of these cases are common administrative restarts for tournament games.
 *
 * For 3v3s and 4v4s, custom placement is used to determine the positions of
 * players. In the past, there were reports of a lack of randomness, with the
 * same flank players matched up against each other repeatedly. The changes
 * to positioning seem to have fixed these issues.
 *
 * Since Black Forest traditionally is played on the Explored visibility
 * settings, this map script makes that setting the default, even if the
 * Reveal Map option is set to Normal in the lobby. This change is intended
 * to prevent errors during tournament matches, in case the lobby members
 * do not notice the incorrect visibility is selected. This change is
 * implemented by setting the same player resource that is set by the
 * Portuguese Circumnavigation technology.
 *
 * Further, this map script disables the ability of Fishing Ships to regarrison
 * within Docks and disables the ability of Docks with garrisoned Fishing Ships
 * to shoot arrows.
 *
 * Further, due to feedback around the time of the release of the
 * Three Kingdoms DLC, predators are changed to have a smaller radius and to
 * behave the same way as Wolves. These changes are to ensure consistency with
 * quick-walling predators and to enable the usage of different predator
 * graphics while maintaining the same gameplay experience as Wolves.
 *
 * The 1v1 version of the map also does not have any predators.
 */

#MKCONSTS

/* Player resource changed by the Portuguese Circumnavigation technology. */
#const CIRCUMNAVIGATION_RESOURCE 203

/* Placeholder constants. */
#const PHON 1543
#const PHONL 1544

/* Malay Harbors, used for disabling re-garrisoning of Fishing Ships. */
#const HARBOR 1189

/* Ship constants for the Dock arrow change. */
